subsection.def:
agreed fare arrangement (協定車費安排), in relation to a fleet taxi, means an
                arrangement to hire the taxi for a pre-arranged journey for an agreed fare;
                    (34 of 2023 s. 14)

fleet taxi (車隊的士)
                means a taxi the registration mark of which is specified in a taxi fleet licence;
                    (34 of 2023 s. 14)

hirer
                    (租用人) includes a person intending to seek
                hire;

subparagraph.content:
does not relate to a passenger service licence
                                                currently in force in respect of the vehicle;
                                                or

subsection.def:
e-certificate (電子證明書)
                                means a certificate issued under subregulation (1) that is issued in
                                the form of an electronic record;

paragraph.content:
the vehicle requirements of the taxis (including requirements relating to
                    the age, type and carrying capacity of the taxis and the equipment or devices to
                    be installed on the taxis);

section.def:
applicant
                (申請人) means an applicant for a hire car
            permit;

paragraph.content:
the vehicle licence of the private car in respect of which the hire car
                    permit is issued is suspended under section 93 of the Ordinance;
                    or

the hire car permit ceases to be valid under regulation 18;
                    (L.N. 196 of
                    2022)

must ensure that all exits of the vehicle, including emergency exits, are
